2026-03-11 | Find Complement of an Integer

	Question
Return the complement of integer n.

	Approach
1.	Find the smallest number that has all bits set to 1 and covers the binary length of n.
2.	This mask can be built as:
		mask = (1 << number_of_bits) - 1
3.	The complement is then:
		mask XOR n
4.	This flips only the bits used by n.

	Time Complexity
	O(log n)

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int findComplement(int n) {
        int mask = 1;

        while (mask <= n)
            mask <<= 1;

        mask -= 1;

        return mask ^ n;
    }
};

	Key Insight
If we create a mask of all 1s that matches the length of n's binary representation,  
then XOR with n flips all its bits, giving the complement.
